<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-08 02:38 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7886 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s BC-BKN-LAKERS-PACERS2-LA     06-08 0641
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-PACERS2-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
REGGIE WAS A NO-SHOW IN GAME 1
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By STEVE DILBECK  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The go-to guy was gone. He was somewhere else.
There was somebody in Reggie Miller's uniform, just not anyone that
could be recognized.
</P>
<P>
   Reggie Miller doesn't go 1 for 16 from the field. He doesn't
miss every single jumpshot. Doesn't enter the wrong side of the
playoff record books.
</P>
<P>
   But there was Miller _ the man who stared down New York _
crumbling back home in his first appearance in the NBA Finals.
</P>
<P>
   Miller, the Riverside product and former UCLA star, was shooting
.466 percent from the field in the playoffs and leading the Pacers
with a 23.8 scoring average. Then, in the biggest game of his life,
he was a no-show.
</P>
<P>
   In a 104-87 loss to the Lakers Wednesday in the opener of the
Finals, Reggie Miller, one of the great shooters in NBA history,
hit one layup in 16 field goal attempts.
</P>
<P>
   And afterward he was... well, defiant.
</P>
<P>
   ``I couldn't put the ball in the basket, but I'll tell you what
_ if they keep giving me those looks, they're going to be in
trouble,'' Miller said.
</P>
<P>
   ``My first four baskets went in and out, and every shot but one
felt good. If they're going to play me like that, it's only a
matter of time.''
</P>
<P>
   See, Miller's a shooter and that's the way shooters think.
That's the way Pacers coach Larry Bird wants him to think.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not uncommon for a guy in his first Finals, after he's
carried us all the way and led the offense, to go out and struggle
a bit in the first game,'' Bird said.
</P>
<P>
   ``He kept battling, he kept shooting. All Reggie has to do is
make a couple and he'll be back.
</P>
<P>
   ``In the playoffs he's been awesome. He had one bad shooting
night. There's no one giving up on him. We want him to continue to
shoot if he has the shot. We don't like him to force things.''
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers would like to take a lot of credit for the
outstanding defensive job they did on him, and they did play him
fairly well, but mostly he just missed ... and missed.
</P>
<P>
   Ron Harper, who spent many a season guarding Miller while with
the Bulls, started on Miller. Kobe Bryant and Brian Shaw also took
turns on him.
</P>
<P>
   But the way he was going, the Lakers could have guarded him with
Tex Winter. Miller kept firing and the ball kept hitting rim and
not net.
</P>
<P>
   His 1-for-16 shooting night was the sixth worst in NBA Finals
history for players who attempted at least 10 field goals. His
final seven points was a career playoff low. And he did his best to
shrug it all off.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is going to be a long series,'' Miller said. ``It's what
adjustments you make and what you do the day after the game. So I'm
looking forward to it. Just one of those off nights. And Friday
will be our night.''
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers, too, are not counting on winning by watching Miller
go into the tank again.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've never really seen him off for two games, so we know he's
going to come to play on Friday,'' said Lakers center Shaquille
O'Neal. ``We have to be ready for that.''
</P>
<P>
   Said Harper: ``His shot just didn't fall.''
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers kept giving Miller the baseline, which he kept
driving to no avail.
</P>
<P>
   ``You can't just settle for jumpshots,'' Miller said. ``If
they're going to continue to give me baseline, I'm going to take it
every time.''
</P>
<P>
   And Miller almost sneered when it was suggested the Lakers
played him physically.
</P>
<P>
   ``It wasn't physical at all,'' he said. ``Our last two series,
those were physical. This is nothing.''
</P>
<P>
   Miller might have appeared to press, but he claimed otherwise.
</P>
<P>
   ``You really can't press on wide-open looks,'' he said. ``I feel
bad I only got off 16 shots. If I was going to be 1 for 16, I
should have been something like 1 for 25 or something.
</P>
<P>
   ``Shooters shoot.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
