<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-08 12:12 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A8033 &Cx1f; tab-z
u k BC-ROEPER-DEATH-DOTCOM-C     06-08 1071
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ROEPER-DEATH-DOTCOM-COLUMN-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BEER AND LOATHING IN LAS VEGAS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use Thursday, June 8, or thereafter.)  
 ATTENTION EDITORS: The following material from The New York Times
Syndicate is for use by clients of the ROEPER-COLUMN.
Nonsubscribers can use this article only by special arrangement.
For purchase information, see end of text. 
 By RICHARD ROEPER  
 c.2000 The Chicago Sun-Times  
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features)  
<TEXT>
<P>
   In the 21st century, few concepts are so insane as to be
completely discounted.
</P>
<P>
   The reality of our political scandals, our hit TV shows, our
sensational murder cases, transcends almost any threshold of
disbelief. Unless we hear that Jesus is playing the World Music
Theater in Tinley Park (``He sold out faster than Buffet!'') or
Regis Philbin has mastered the art of flying by flapping his arms
really fast, we're not really surprised by anything any more.
</P>
<P>
   It sounds like an oxymoron, but we're gullible cynics. Hardly
anything surprises us, so we question the veracity of few things.
For example, would you be shocked if I told you about plans for a
chain of funeral theme parks?
</P>
<P>
   We live in a country where the Key West experience is sanitized
in a Key West theme park 300 miles from the real Key West. Where a
half-sized Eiffel Tower and a near-replica of the Statue of Liberty
rise above the Strip in Las Vegas. Where you can play the part of a
19th century slave being hunted down in a theme park in Indiana. So
why not a park about the most amazing journey of all?
</P>
<P>
   ``Death faces all of us,'' reads the message on the home page of
the Final Curtain Web site, at www.finalcurtain.com.
</P>
<P>
   ``But there's a lack of imagination which accompanies our
passage. Until now, the handling of death has been regimented and
boring; limited by those who control it, whether the state, church,
morticians or our survivors. At the Final Curtain, we are throwing
away all the rules.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Final Curtain is a series of memorial parks dedicated to
creative souls ... clients are encouraged to develop site-specific
works of passage _ their own tombstones, mausoleums, caskets or
urns _ as homage to their lives and spirit ...''
</P>
<P>
   The web site includes profiles of the Final Curtain's management
team, information for potential investors, links to media coverage,
and maps and descriptions of a typical theme park, with
restaurants, gift shops, galleries, a museum and other
``world-class facilities allowing for a spiritually invigorating
and aesthetically rewarding visit.''
</P>
<P>
   We're talking about features such as the Paradise Museum.
Dante's Grill. The Heaven's Gate Cafe.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Memorial Park is the cemetery proper,'' explains the site.
``This section of the park encompasses the artists' Monument
Gardens as well as the Timeshare Greenhouse and various ...
entertainment areas.''
</P>
<P>
   That's right, timeshare. They're offering you the chance to
``join our timeshare program through which we transport your
remains to several of our parks on a rotational basis.''
</P>
<P>
   You think that's weird, consider the description of the eternal
flame exhibit: ``On a hill overlooking the lake and amphitheater, a
massive rectangular black granite wall stands engraved with the
names of innumerable art critics. At the center of this solitary
structure, a huge menacing flame burns in testament to the vitriol
and spiteful tongues of the not-so-dearly departed. Guests perusing
this structure will find the floor of the monument sloping down
toward the base of the eternal flame. A doorway is located at the
base of the flame and is the entrance to Dante's Grill.''
</P>
<P>
   And then there's the graffiti wall, where visitors can write
their own feelings about death, whether their own or someone
else's. Not to mention the children's playground. Talk about
morbid.
</P>
<P>
   Little wonder that about 40 newspapers, a dozen magazines and
more than 20 radio and TV stations have done stories about the
Final Curtain. The Los Angeles Times, the London Daily Telegraph,
the Boston Herald, NPR, Mother Jones magazine. Even in our crazy,
jaded times, some stories make you shake your head and say, ``Are
you kidding me?''
</P>
<P>
   Well, yes. Turns out The Final Curtain is pure hoax.
</P>
<P>
   But this wasn't the work of some 19-year-old cyberprankster. The
creator of the elaborate Final Curtain hoax was Joey Skaggs, a
professional practical joker who has been yanking media chains for
decades.
</P>
<P>
   I could have fallen for this one myself. I remember seeing a
little item somewhere about the Final Curtain and writing a note to
myself: ``Possible column?'' If I'd logged onto the site, if I'd
interviewed Skaggs posing as one of the executives, if I'd read the
items and stories in The Los Angeles Times and Mother Jones and
heard the report on NPR, I would have been certain about Final
Curtain. And I would have been wrong.
</P>
<P>
   Fortunately for me and for other journalists who hadn't yet been
duped, Skaggs himself blew the whistle with a press release
explaining the joke. Some of the bamboozled reporters took the joke
in good stride; others were outraged.
</P>
<P>
   Either way, the Final Curtain is only a hoax for now. Someday,
somebody will come up with an afterlife theme park. Skaggs may be a
hoaxster, but don't be surprised when he turns out to be a
visionary.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (Richard Roeper (rroeper(at)suntimes.com) is a columnist for
the Chicago Sun-Times and the author, most recently, of ``Urban
Legends: The Truth Behind All Those Deliciously Entertaining Myths
That Are Absolutely, Positively, 100% Not True!'' Roeper is also a
commentator for Fox News in Chicago and has appeared on programs
such as ``Nightline,'' ``The CBS Evening News with Dan Rather,''
``Oprah'' and ``The Drudge Report.'') &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ------------------------------------------------- &QC;
