<HEADLINE>
EVALUATING THE TRAVEL SITES 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Sidebar to Tech-Travel)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The following reviews were written by Stephanie Stoughton of the
Globe staff based on research done at the end of May.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; AUTO RENTAL SITES
</P>
<P>
   Avis
</P>
<P>
   www.avis.com, 800-230-4898
</P>
<P>
   Description: Online automobile rental site.
</P>
<P>
   Ease of use: Speedy but clunky.
</P>
<P>
   Telephone response: Representative answered within three rings
and provided quick, intelligent response.
</P>
<P>
   E-mail response: Six days later and didn't answer the question.
</P>
<P>
   Features: A 15 percent discount on online reservations, local
specials, and bonus airline miles.
</P>
<P>
   Pet peeve: Sometimes refers customers to local offices.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Budget
</P>
<P>
   www.budget.com, 800-527-0700
</P>
<P>
   Description: Rents everything from Ford Escorts to Jaguars.
</P>
<P>
   Ease of use: Experienced many errors while ordering.
</P>
<P>
   Telephone response: Person who answered phone referred us to
another toll-free number, where a representative blamed the errors
on us. Bad customers!
</P>
<P>
   E-mail response: Does not want e-mail from customers right now.
</P>
<P>
   Features: ``Hot deals'' section that has big discounts but takes
too much time to read. But check out the $19.99-a-day promotion on
the Ford Ranger pick-up.
</P>
<P>
   Pet peeve: A Web site that you can't e-mail? Get real.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Enterprise Rent-a-Car
</P>
<P>
   www.enterprise.com, 800-736-8227
</P>
<P>
   Description: Internet auto rental site.
</P>
<P>
   Ease of use: Well-organized store front, but the site has a few
dead-end links and sometimes refers customers to local offices.
</P>
<P>
   Telephone response: Picked up in two rings; knowledgable answer.
</P>
<P>
   E-mail response: No response.
</P>
<P>
   Features: Nothing to distinguish itself from its competitors.
</P>
<P>
   Pet peeve: Where are the big discounts?
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Hertz
</P>
<P>
   www.hertz.com, 800-654-3131
</P>
<P>
   Description: The site of the nation's largest automobile rental
company.
</P>
<P>
   Ease of use: Fast site, but hard to compare automobile makes and
rates.
</P>
<P>
   Telephone response: Answered in two rings with smart service.
</P>
<P>
   E-mail response: Two days; the only car-rental site that
answered an e-mailed question.
</P>
<P>
   Features: Loaded with special offers and discounts.
</P>
<P>
   Pet peeve: Too many clicks and too much needless typing
required.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   National
</P>
<P>
   www.nationalcar.com, 1-888-227-7368
</P>
<P>
   Description: Automobile rental site.
</P>
<P>
   Ease of use: Making an effort to slice through the number of
steps required to make a purchase. But the fancy graphics on the
storefront bogged us down.
</P>
<P>
   Telephone response: A customer representative told us where to
find the e-mail address. When we told her it wasn't there she
insisted we were wrong. ``I know it's there,'' she said. ``I just
don't know what it is.''
</P>
<P>
   E-mail response: Could not locate an e-mail box.
</P>
<P>
   Features: Discounts on online rentals, including 20 percent off
rates through the end of June.
</P>
<P>
   Pet peeve: Finding this company's Web site is no easy task
because a semiconductor company snapped up the national.com
address. National needs to work with search engines to make sure
customers can get to its site.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   AIRLINES
</P>
<P>
   American Airlines
</P>
<P>
   www.aa.com, 800-222-2377
</P>
<P>
   Description: Airline tickets reservation site with links to its
vacation packages.
</P>
<P>
   Ease of use: Some slowness. Trying to book an American Airlines
vacation is no fun.
</P>
<P>
   Telephone response: On hold for four minutes; customer service
representative was polite and informed.
</P>
<P>
   E-mail response: Five days; did not answer the question.
</P>
<P>
   Features: Bonus miles, special fares for members. Customers also
can download flight information onto their hand-held Palm VII
computers.
</P>
<P>
   Pet peeve: Plays hide-and-seek with its 800-number.
