Previewtravel.com and other sites.
</P>
<P>
   Ease of use: Speedy site, but Travelocity.com needs to clear its
cluttered storefront.
</P>
<P>
   Telephone response: On hold for seven minutes with feel-good
music: ``Feel all right now'' and ``Chickee-chickee-oww.''
</P>
<P>
   E-mail response: We didn't find the e-mail box in time.
</P>
<P>
   Features: Nice quick getaways. Lists hotels by availability, so
you don't have to waste your time going down the list (like you do
on Expedia.com).
</P>
<P>
   Pet peeve: We initially missed the company's e-mail
customer-service box because it's at the bottom of a Web page. In
the meantime, we puttered around, mistakenly hit a Radisson link
and ended up with the hotel's customer service people. Radisson
e-mailed us back in two days and informed us of the boo-boo.
</P>
