what it once was, and now there are grand plans from City Hall: a
$31 million sea-front stadium; $30 million more for amateur sports
facilities; and another $30 million for a boardwalk facelift. By
David Barstow.
</P>
<P>
   NY-HOTEL-CBS (New York) _ A crowd peering in from the sidewalk
is a signature of NBC's Today Show. Even ABC's Good Morning America
draws pretty good window crowds in Times Square these days. So
Bryant Gumbel's Early Show on CBS decided to try the same thing by
having bands play in the morning in front of the studio in the
General Motors building at Fifth Avenue and 59th Street. But the
bands wake up the guests at the grand Sherry Netherland across the
street, and today the hotel is taking CBS to court. By Nadine
Brozan.
