company warns of a flat fourth quarter. (Analysts had been
expecting a 16 percent rise in profit from a year ago.) Alan
Lafley, 52, head of P&AMP;G's global beauty care business, is named
chief executive. By David Leonhardt.
</P>
<P>
   DIGITAL-HOLLYWOOD (Los Angeles) _ Over the last year or so, the
worlds of old-line Hollywood and the dot-coms of the new economy
have been intermingling with increasing urgency, taking their first
faltering steps toward the coming age of digital entertainment,
whatever that might turn out to be. While the major studios,
conservative as always, are largely maintaining a discrete distance
from the roiling waters of the Web, many entertainment executives,
filmmakers, celebrities and talent agencies have been plunging
head-first into the digital deep end. By Rick Lyman.
</P>
