   SNAPSHOTS-MET (New York) _ Family snapshots have become art in a
highly unusual and sublimely endearing exhibition called ``Other
Pictures: Vernacular Photographs From the Thomas Walther
Collection'' at the Metropolitan Museum of Art. By Michael
Kimmelman.
</P>
<P>
   PA-COAL-MINES (Scranton, Pa.) _ The hundreds of visitors who
take the guided tours at the Lackawanna Coal Mine every day are
meant to come back into the sunshine with a greater appreciation of
a way of life that left deep veins of loss, misery and cultural
trauma through successive generations of families in the anthracite
fields of Northeast Pennsylvania. By Joe Sharkey.
</P>
