   PIMP-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``American Pimp,'' a terse,
skillfully edited documentary by the Hughes Brothers (Allen and
Albert), is a breezy montage of interviews with pimps of varying
ages in several U.S. cities that purports to uncover the realities
behind the myths surrounding those flamboyantly attired street
hustlers. Reviewed by Stephen Holden.
</P>
<P>
   CHABANNES-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``The Children of Chabannes,''
a documentary, was made by Dean Wetherell and Lisa Gosselsa and is
a moving record of the heroism of ordinary people in the village of
Chabannes who gave refuge to nearly 400 Jewish children, protecting
them from the Nazis. Reviewed by A.O. Scott.
</P>
