by Peter Wintonick asks whether cinema verite is a style or a
movement; a technique or a philosophy; or, as Frederick Wiseman,
one of its great avatars, suggested, a piece of ``pretentious and
pompous'' French jargon? Reviewed by A.O. Scott.
</P>
