<HEADLINE>
DUKE ELLINGTON ORCHESTRA SINGER'S RECORDINGS AVAILABLE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: In the early '50s, my favorite singer was Herb Jeffries. All
my 78s are gone. Is any of his work available now?
</P>
<P>
   _ P.F., Clifton, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   A: At least two recordings by the former Duke Ellington
Orchestra performer are in print: ``Bronze Buckaroo,'' a 1995
collection of 10 western songs, and ``The Duke and I'' from 1999.
</P>
<P>
   ``Buckaroo'' is available by mail for $10.98 on tape or $15.98
on CD. Order from Real West Productions, Four Winds Trading Co.,
635 S. Broadway, Suite E, Boulder, CO 80303, or call (800)
456-5444.
</P>
<P>
   ``Duke'' can be ordered on CD from Jeffries for $16 plus $2.95
shipping and handling. Write to Flaming-O Productions, 44-489 Town
Center Way, PMB D-492, Palm Desert, CA 92260, or visit the Web site
www.herbjeffries.com.
</P>
<P>
   Jeffries, 88, continues to make public appearances and tour.
Next on the schedule is an Aug. 26 performance at the Jazz in the
Pines festival in Idyllwild, Calif.
</P>
<P>
   Q: My husband is looking for a leather belt that has a secret
compartment on the inside for money. Where can I buy one?
</P>
<P>
   _ P.H., Ripley, Mass.
</P>
<P>
   A: Sova Leather in San Francisco sells a unisex black leather
belt in sizes 32 through 42 for $19 plus $4.95 shipping and
handling. The 1 1/4-inch-wide belt has a hidden 15-inch-long pocket
that zips closed.
</P>
<P>
   To order, call Sova at (415) 626-8899 on business days from 1 to
6 p.m. or visit the Web site www.sovaleather.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where could I write to Meg Ryan?
</P>
<P>
   _ M.M., Euless, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Send your letter in care of International Creative
Management, 8942 Wilshire Blvd., Beverly Hills, CA 90211.
</P>
<P>
   Earlier this year, Ryan appeared in ``Hanging Up'' with Lisa
Kudrow and Diane Keaton, who also directed the film. Her next
picture is ``Proof of Life,'' a hostage drama that also stars
Russell Crowe and David Caruso.
</P>
<P>
   Ryan, 38, is limiting herself to one film per year so she can
spend more time with son Jack, 8, and husband Dennis Quaid.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
