<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    ALBANIAN REBELS REARM TO LIBERATE KOSOVO
 &HT;    With KOSOVO-TENSIONS
 &HT;    With Photo
 &HT;    Advance for use Sunday, June 11
 &HT;    By MARGARET COKER
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service(at) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   DOBROSIN, Yugoslavia _ The sun glared down on the clay-baked
courtyard as a mother and father in their Sunday best, fidgeting
and nervously chatting with two armed guards, waited for the
Albanian rebel leader to appear.
</P>
<P>
   The parents were searching for their 17-year-old son who had run
away from home. They heard that he and two friends had come here to
Dobrosin, a village located in the demilitarized zone between
Kosovo and Serbia, to sign up with an illegal branch of the Kosovo
Liberation Army.
</P>
<P>
   According to U.S. military intelligence, the one-story adobe
compound where they waited anxiously is home for as many as 150
battle-ready Albanian fighters.
</P>
<P>
   When the trim, bearded rebel commander showed up after 30
minutes,
</P>
