<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ROCKER _ TOLEDO _ TOLEDO, Ohio _ Atlanta Braves relief
pitcher John Rocker joins the Atlanta Braves' Richmond farm team in
Toledo for tonight's game against the Mudhens. (Curtright, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-LAKERS-SUCCESS _ Now that the Lakers have won the first game
of the NBA Finals, they face another important question - how are
they going to handle their success? In each of their three previous
playoff series, the Lakers have had trouble handling success. They
lost a 2-0 lead before winning a decisive game against Sacramento,
failed to put Phoenix away when they lead 3-0 and lost a 3-1 lead
before defeating Portland. The Lakers hope to put their struggles
behind them Friday and win Game 2 before the series shifts to
Indianapolis. (Bunn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BKN-PACERS _ The Pacers were victimized by one of the most
dominating performances in NBA Finals history in Game 1 as
Shaquille O'Neal had 43 points and 19 rebounds. Now the Pacers are
searching for ways to contain O'Neal, if it's possible. The Pacers
tried to defend O'Neal with Rik Smits, but O'Neal answered with 19
first-quarter points. The Pacers might attempt to double and
triple-team O'Neal in Game 2 as they look to remain in the series.
(Denberg, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
