<P>
   SCI-INSECTICIDE (Undated) _ One of the most common ingredients
in home, lawn and garden bug killers poses an unacceptable health
risk, particularly to children, and will no longer be manufactured
for that use by the end of the year, environmental officials said
Thursday. The insecticide, also called Dursban, has been widely
used for more than 30 years both in agriculture and in products
used by exterminators and homeowners, including more than a dozen
kinds of Raid sprays, Hartz yard and kennel flea spray, and Black
Flag liquid roach and ant killer. By Andrew C. Revkin.
