<TEXT>
<P>
   The Hollywood Garage Sale: A series of auctions of Hollywood
collectibles and set visits, sponsored by broadband service
provider Excitehome and the Entertainment Industry Foundation, to
benefit the Juvenile Diabetes Foundation. &QL; 
Where: http://auctions.excite.com &QL; 
What's cool: The Juvenile Diabetes Foundation is guaranteed $1
million from the auction by Excite, even if people don't buy any of
the 150 different goodies for sale. But there's sure to be plenty
to interest hard-core entertainment fans, as the auctions are
broken into four themed two-week sales. &QL; 
Features: The offerings include a costume from ``Gladiator'';
wedding dresses worn by Meg Ryan, Sharon Stone and Nicole Kidman
in, respectively, ``Sleepless in Seattle,'' ``Casino'' and ``To Die
For''; a trip to the London set of ``The Mummy 2''; a day on ``The
Today Show'' set; the red dress Michelle Pfeiffer wore in ``The
Fabulous Baker Boys''; a visit with Sela Ward and the set of ``Once
and Again''; and a uniform from ``Star Trek: Voyager'' among much
else. &QL; 
You'll like this if: You're sweet on kids, and on cool Hollywood
stuff. &QL; 
