<P>
   CLARK-WARCRIMES (Washington) _ Army Gen. Wesley Clark, the
former NATO commander who the led last year's successful military
campaign to expel Serbian forces from Kosovo, defends himself
against Amnesty International charges that he was responsible for
war crimes. The human rights group cited him for ordering the
bombing of a Serbian TV station that killed 16 civilians. But Clark
insists that ``it was a legitimate military target,'' the
propaganda machine of Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic. By ERIC
ROSENBERG. (Already filed.)
