<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following story
for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of Friday,
June 9, and thereafter. This story is an addition to the budget
that moved earlier. If you have any questions, please call Larry
Johnson on the national-foreign desk at (206) 448-8035.
</P>
<P>
   MURDER-CIRCUMSTANTIAL (Undated) _ A Redmond, Wash., man was
convicted Thursday of first-degree murder in the death of his wife,
who disappeared nearly 10 years ago. Prosecutors built the case
against Steven Sherer entirely on circumstantial evidence, since
the victim's body was never found.
</P>
<P>
   By Tracy Johnson. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
