<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRUMP-LANDSCAPE0609-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Trump hopes to cut a deal on landscaping
 &HT;    By Trebor Banstetter
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Donald Trump is hoping his deal-making
prowess can get him out of county rules forcing him to landscape a
section of Congress Avenue fronting his new $40 million golf club.
</P>
<P>
   It appears the projected $300,000 price tag is too rich for
Trump's blood.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's much higher than the $6,000 we had originally planned,''
said land planner Bob Bentz, who is representing Trump. ``That's
why we're working to come up with some alternative.''
</P>
<P>
   After months of delays, county commissioners are scheduled to
vote on Trump's appeal June 29. Trump's representatives have been
lobbying the county _ particularly Commissioner Carol Roberts _
since September to bend the rules for him.
</P>
<P>
   The celebrity developer argues that the county's new law, which
requires builders to landscape medians on roads adjacent to their
developments, was unfairly applied to his suburban West Palm Beach
golf course.
</P>
<P>
   Trump began building his lavish Trump International Golf Club
long before the landscaping rules were passed. But in September the
new law came into effect for him because he made changes to the
design of the golf course.
</P>
<P>
   The changes affected just more than 1 acre of the property,
enough to trigger the median rule.
</P>
<P>
   ``They were very minor changes,'' acknowledged Haney Frakes, the
assistant county engineer. ``It was just over the threshold.''
</P>
<P>
   Under the law, Trump must install landscaping along the medians
of Congress Avenue from Summit Boulevard to Gun Club Road.
</P>
<P>
   Complicating matters, the state Department of Transportation has
just built concrete traffic separators along the road.
</P>
<P>
   To tear those out, plant grass and bushes and install an
underground irrigation system would cost between $250,000 and
$300,000, Bentz said.
</P>
<P>
   The county's zoning commission, an advisory board, said in
September that Trump should follow the rules and make the
improvements.
</P>
<P>
   His hearing before county commissioners, who make the final
decision, has been delayed for months.
</P>
<P>
   But when he does finally go before commissioners, a deferral
from the law may be a tough sell.
</P>
<P>
   ``The rules should be equally applied to anybody who modifies or
improves their development,'' said Commissioner Warren Newell. ``We
can't just go making exceptions for one guy, no matter who he is.''
</P>
<P>
   Trump plans to offer commissioners an alternative: Landscaping
the median along a shorter, more northern stretch of Congress.
</P>
<P>
   Bentz didn't have a price tag for Trump's alternative, but said
it ``would certainly be cheaper'' than $300,000.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're going to provide (the county) with the details next week
and have it before commissioners later this month,'' Bentz said.
``We think this is a fair way to work this out.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
