<HEADLINE>
PULVERIZED PACERS TRYING TO SLOW DOWN O'NEAL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DWAIN PRICE 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ In Game 1 of the NBA Finals, Shaquille O'Neal
rumbled through Indiana with such force that the Pacers probably
felt as though they were in an earthquake.
</P>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Lakers center scored 43 points and overpowered
them for 19 rebounds, as the Lakers shook up the Pacers in winning
the opener of the best-of-seven championship series, 104-87.
</P>
<P>
   So what's a Pacer to do in order to prevent another devastating
attack from Shaq in Game 2 at 8 tonight at the Staples Center?
</P>
<P>
   ``After the way Shaquille laid us up \RWednesday\S night,
obviously we're going to try to be more aggressive,'' Pacers coach
Larry Bird said. ``We got there on the double teams, but it wasn't
aggressive.
</P>
<P>
   ``If you come down there soft on him, he'll make you pay for it
every time.''
</P>
<P>
   Rik Smits was no match for O'Neal as he fouled out trying to
defend the self-proclaimed ``Big Aristotle.'' Sam Perkins and Dale
Davis also tried to guard O'Neal.
</P>
<P>
   Asked how he would defend himself, O'Neal said: ``I wouldn't. I
would just go home. Or fake an injury or something.''
</P>
<P>
   Bird said there will be situations where he'll advise his team
to intentionally foul O'Neal so he has to work on his weak
free-throw shooting. O'Neal, who was only 1-of-6 from the
free-throw line in Game 1, bristled at that philosophy.
</P>
<P>
   ``It hasn't worked yet,'' he said. ``So, no need for me to make
it work now.''  &QL; 
Jackson thrives
</P>
<P>
   Lost in Shaquille O'Neal's performance in Game 1 and Reggie
Miller's off night was the fact that Pacers point guard Mark
Jackson played perhaps his best game of this year's playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   Jackson was 6-of-8 from the field and contributed seven assists
and five rebounds in 28 minutes. He was playing in the late crucial
minutes, a time when Jackson is normally on the bench in favor of
Travis Best.
</P>
<P>
   Jackson was glad he was able to show he still can be efficient
at critical moments.
</P>
<P>
   ``The main thing is they're trying to disrupt our offense,'' he
said. ``But all I have to do is remain aggressive and try to put
pressure on them offensively.''  &QL; 
Miller: Lakers not tough
</P>
<P>
   Reggie Miller dismissed the Lakers as anything but a physical
team.
</P>
<P>
   ``They weren't physical at all,'' Miller said of the Lakers'
Game 1 showing. ``Our last two series \Ragainst New York and
Philadelphia\S were physical. This is nothing.'' Former TCU
standout guard Mike Jones scored a team-high 18 points in leading
the NBA Ambassadors to a one-sided 96-74 victory over the CTBA
all-stars in a game played yesterday in Asia.
</P>
<P>
   The game was the opener of a 20-game season for the
Ambassadors.]  &QL; 
Briefly
</P>
<P>
   The bad news for the Pacers is that in their 15-year history
playing in the NBA, they are 0-11 in playoff series in which they
lost Game 1.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers have won Game 1 won three championships.
</P>
<P>
   nn
</P>
</TEXT>
