r s BC-CAR-IRL-NASCAR-TEX     06-08 0396
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CAR-IRL-NASCAR-TEX </SLUG>
 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOHNNY PAUL 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Eddie Cheever describes the International
Race of Champions series as ``racing against the good ol' boys in
good ol' boys' cars.''
</P>
<P>
   NASCAR's ``good ol' boys'' will race at their convenience, too.
</P>
<P>
   The third leg of the IROC series will be contested tomorrow at
Michigan Speedway, site of the Winston Cup Kmart 400 on Sunday.
That means Cheever, Mark Dismore and Plano's Greg Ray will be
forced into double duty with the Casino Magic 500 scheduled
tomorrow night at Texas Motor Speedway.
</P>
<P>
   The three Indy Racing League drivers plan to practice until 5:15
tonight at Texas Motor Speedway's 1.5-mile quadoval before
departing for Brooklyn, Mich., to compete in tomorrow's 11 a.m.
IROC race.
</P>
<P>
   ``I really, really enjoy it,'' Cheever said of the IROC series,
``but it is a bit of a pain in the butt.''
</P>
<P>
   Cheever, Dismore and Ray plan to fly to Michigan tonight on the
Challenger jet of IRL founder Tony George. The three plan to return
to Fort Worth tomorrow afternoon on George's jet before racing in
the Casino Magic 500, scheduled for 7 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   ``The IRL is my primary series, and it's going to be a little
bit of a physical struggle,'' Ray said. ``First time I've done two
races in a single day on opposite ends of the country.''
</P>
<P>
   Why would a driver put himself through such a harried day?
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a pain,'' Cheever said, ``but I'm happy to be doing it
because the IROC is a very prestigious series.''
</P>
<P>
   The IROC series pits drivers from the IRL and NASCAR's Winston
Cup Series in 12 identically prepared Pontiac Firebirds. The
four-race series concludes Aug. 4 at Indianapolis Motor Speedway.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have a pretty hectic lifestyle,'' Ray said. ``The thing is
knowing you have good people around you, and it's a lot easier to
handle when you're confident that you have good cars and people
around you and you do what you do _ and that's drive the race car.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's prestigious for me, and whether you finish first, fifth
or last, all you can do is critique what you've done and try to
learn. With having a race later in the day, it puts a premium on
not getting hurt.''
</P>
<P>
   So, what effect will the doubleheader have on the three IRL
drivers?
</P>
<P>
   ``If I fare well,'' Ray said, ``I can see doing it in the
future.''
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-08-00 2310EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
