<SLUG> BC-SOROS-RUSSIA-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RUSSIA IMPRESSES SOROS  

</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   MOSCOW _ George Soros, who owns one of the biggest failed
investments in Russia, said Thursday that he was impressed with the
country's economic improvement and the new administration's
apparent willingness to protect investors.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm ready to invest more in Russia,'' he said at a news
conference here. ``The economy's doing very well. There's genuine
growth. There are opportunities for those who are strong-hearted.''
</P>
<P>
   Soros has sunk more than $1 billion into commercial investments
in Russia. Most of that is stuck in an ill-fated purchase of a
stake in the main state telephone holding company he has called
``the worst investment decision of my career.'' The 25 percent
stake is currently worth less than half of what it was in 1997 when
he purchased it through a group called Mustcom Ltd. Now, he said,
he is not ruling out further purchases in the company.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
